==English==
===Etymology===
From Sanskrit [[पंच]] (pa.nća) (''five'') + Persian {{FAchar|[[اب|آب]]}} (āb) (''water'') = ''The Land of Five Rivers'' + Persic adjectival form {{FAchar|[[ی]]}} (ī).
===Pronunciation===
*po͝on-jä'bi, {{Unicode|/pʊnˌdʒɑːbi/}}, /<tt>pUn"dZA:bi</tt>/

===Adjective===
'''Punjabi'''

# Of, pertaining to, descended from the people or culture of the [[Punjab]], or written in the Punjabi language

===Noun===
'''Punjabi'''

# Language spoken in Northern [[India]] and Eastern [[Pakistan]]
# Resident of or immigrant from the Punjab (often, loosely, "Sikh")

====Alternative spellings====
*[[Panjabi]]

